# Flutter Patterns

- Widgets (especially `StatelessWidget`) are immutable; Flutter rebuilds the widget tree when UI must change
- Prefer composing smaller widgets over extending existing ones. Use small `Widget` classes instead of private helper methods that return a `Widget`
- Break down large `build()` methods into smaller, reusable Widget classes
- Use `ListView.builder` for lazy-loaded lists. Use `const` constructors in widgets and in `build()` whenever possible
- Avoid expensive operations (network calls, complex computation) inside `build()` methods
- Favor isolated widget files over private _build widgets; user prefers isolated widgets in their own files with pages calling those widgets
- Aim for separation of concerns (MVC/MVVM). For shared/complex state use `ChangeNotifier`; for robust structure use MVVM with Repositories/Services for data sources
